Residents of Bunyala Central ward, Budalang’i in Busia county on Sunday were cautioned against eating dead birds killed by a poisonous birds spray. Busia Deputy Governor Moses Mulomi told residents the poisonous insecticide sprayed on all destructive birds’ spots in the area might cause death. Mulomi also promised residents that the county will consider and act on the appeal of area MCA Felix Omanyi who had called upon the county to set aside capital to facilitate the purchase of a big rice processing machine Once acquired and installed, the rice processing machine would enable farmers to package and brand the rice before selling it.